## Description: What is it? (max 1,500 characters)



This model of financial education is based on using gaming and digital apps to foster the learning experience of children and teenagers. Play as a teaching strategy encourages the application of knowledge in real-life situations. Thus, initiating mechanisms that facilitate the internalization and development of financial skills. Additionally, apps can develop learning processes useful for digital financial tools.

## Purpose: Why do we use this method or tool for R&amp;D? (max 1,500 characters)



This model can be used to tackle the knowledge gaps that prevent people from building financial resilience. Particularly, this model helps you and your partners to start working on financial education with children at school. Moreover, by boosting effective financial literacy, this model can promote and support financial inclusion initiatives.

## Summary: Describe in one sentence, what it is and what it does? (max 120 characters)



It is a model for financial education through play.

## Instructions: How is it used for R&amp;D? What steps to follow?



This model is based on an app design for smartphones. So, the first step to follow is deciding whether you will develop the learning app in-house, or you will partner with an external provider. Based on that decision, you will have to deploy actions to either develop the app on your own or procure it from an established provider.

## Requirements: What is needed to effectively use it for R&amp;D? (e.g. skills, conditions, inputs, resources)



This model works effectively in communities with reliable Internet connectivity and access to smart devices suitable for running the learning app. In addition, it is important to have either the necessary mobile app development experts within your team or the option to outsource the learning app development. Moreover, this model is most useful when it is possible to establish working partnerships with educational communities.

## Reflections: What to keep in mind when using the tool for R&amp;D purposes?



A lack of reliable connectivity and other technological shortcomings can affect the performance of the model. This does not mean that the model implementation is impossible, but rather that effective strategies will be necessary to address these technological challenges.

# Citizen Science and gamification using digital platform to crowdsource solutions

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Reference: Where can we find more information or download materials?

## Description: What is it? (max 1,500 characters)

This is a digital platform that aims to leverage on citizen science and also integrate gamification features to encourage more innovators to share their ideas and solutions. this platform serves as an interactive database for all the ideas and solutions generated from all parts of the country.

## Purpose: Why do we use this method or tool for R&amp;D? (max 1,500 characters)

this method is a bottom-up approach to collate ideas and solutions for some of the development challenges within the country and it also captures not just the solutions but also issues/problems which the policy makers can use to validate the annual progresses made by districts as part of their annual development plan progresses. this aims to live the true meaning of 'not reinventing the wheel'

## Summary: Describe in one sentence, what it is and what it does? (max 120 characters)

Database for ideas/solutions and issues/challenges within the country

## Instructions: How is it used for R&amp;D? What steps to follow?

the platform helps identify ideas and solutions without having to go to the field every single time for solution mapping

## Requirements: What is needed to effectively use it for R&amp;D? (e.g. skills, conditions, inputs, resources)

inclusiveness is key and ensure all stakeholders are engaged from the very beginning in terms of prototyping and user testing. local governments engagement is also key and champions at the local level is critical to map local solutions and upload on the platform.

## Reflections: What to keep in mind when using the tool for R&amp;D purposes?

the platform has to be agile and adaptive to the changing situation and need
